        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: recover terminal session status on visible inbound turns",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #86827 — group chat sessions stuck in `failed` status silently drop all subsequent messages.\n\nWhen a group chat session enters a terminal status (`failed`, `timeout`, or `killed`), the reply dispatch path returns a successful no-op (`queuedFinal: false`, zero dispatch counts) without starting an AI turn or delivering any user-visible error. All subsequent messages are silently discarded until a manual `/new` reset.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThree independent mechanisms conspire to create the silent drop:\n\n1. **Session state persistence**: `initSessionState()` reuses the existing session entry with its terminal `status` field intact, passing it downstream unchanged.\n2. **Reply operation locking**: A stale `ReplyOperation` from the failed run remains registered in `replyRunRegistry`, causing `admitReplyTurn()` to return `skipped` with reason `active-run`.\n3. **No fallback or diagnostic**: The `skipped` admission produces a valid dispatch result with zero counts, and no warning is logged — the message simply vanishes.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Auto-recover terminal sessions (`session.ts`)\n\nWhen a **visible** (non-cron/heartbeat) inbound message hits a session with recoverable terminal status, automatically clear the stale lifecycle fields (`status`, `startedAt`, `endedAt`, `runtimeMs`, `abortedLastRun`) while **preserving the `sessionId` and transcript continuity** — no session rotation.\n\n### 2. Clear stale reply operations (`dispatch-from-config.ts`)\n\nWhen `admitReplyTurn()` returns `skipped` with reason `active-run` but the persisted session is in terminal status, force-clear the stale reply operation via `forceClearReplyRunBySessionId()` and retry admission **once**. This breaks the deadlock without risking infinite retry loops.\n\n### 3. Agent API path (`agent.ts`)\n\nMirror the same terminal recovery logic in the agent API dispatch path so agent API requests also clear terminal state for visible requests.\n\n### 4. Diagnostics (`kernel.ts`, `types.ts`)\n\nAdd a structured warning log when a visible channel turn dispatch completes with `queuedFinal: false` and zero tool/block/final counts — a sentinel for future silent message drops. Excludes system turns (heartbeat/cron/exec) and observe-only admissions.\n\n## Tests\n\n- **session.test.ts**: Verify failed group sessions recover without rotating the transcript\n- **dispatch-from-config.test.ts**: Verify stale active reply operations are cleared for terminal sessions and admission is retried\n- **agent.test.ts**: Verify terminal failed agent API sessions recover without session rotation; updated existing failed-session tests to verify terminal state clearing\n- **kernel.test.ts**: Verify zero-count visible dispatch warning is emitted\n\nAll focused tests pass across 3 Vitest shards (287 + 29 cases).",
